If you are familiar with other shells or programming languages, you might find this chapter useful to get up to speed.
[link: coming_from_bash.md] Coming from Bash
 shows how some patterns typical for Bash, or POSIX shells in general, can be mapped to Nushell.

Similarly, 
[link: coming_from_cmd.md] Coming from CMD.EXE
 shows how built-in commands in the Windows Command Prompt can be mapped to Nushell.
Similar comparisons are made for some 
[link: nushell_map.md] other shells and domain-specific languages
, 
[link: nushell_map_imperative.md] imperative languages
, and 
[link: nushell_map_functional.md] functional languages
.

A separate comparison is made specifically for 
[link: nushell_operator_map.md] operators
.
